Parricidam] “Unnatural murderer.” This epithet is applied to any monstrous criminal : as Catil. 14. omnes un- dique parricidae, sacrilegi, convicti judiciis: but more particu- larly to traitors against the state, slayers of their country, Cic. in Catil. i. 7. te patria odit ac metuit, ac jam diu te nihil judicat nisi de parricidio suo cogitare. 20. Ruina restinguam] Just as a conflagration may be extinguished by the falling or pulling down of the house.
